{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "eazyvtc-promo-codes-sprint6",
    "name": "EazyVTC API — Codes Promo (Sprint 6)",
    "description": "# EazyVTC — Module Codes Promo\n\n## Endpoints couverts\n\n### Admin (CRUD)\n- `GET    /admin/promo-codes`          → Liste paginée (filtres : is_active)\n- `GET    /admin/promo-codes/:id`      → Détail d'un code\n- `POST   /admin/promo-codes`          → Créer un code\n- `PATCH  /admin/promo-codes/:id`      → Modifier / activer / désactiver\n- `DELETE /admin/promo-codes/:id`      → Supprimer\n\n### Client (validation avant réservation)\n- `POST /promo-codes/validate`         → Vérifier un code et calculer la remise\n\n## Logique métier clé\n\n### Types de remise\n| discount_type | Calcul | Exemple |\n|---|---|---|\n| `percent` | `order_amount × (discount_value / 100)` | 10% sur 80€ = 8€ |\n| `fixed` | `discount_value` déduit du montant | 5€ de remise |\n\n### Contraintes\n- `discount_type = percent` → `discount_value` ≤ 100\n- `valid_until` doit être postérieur à `valid_from`\n- `max_uses` null = utilisations illimitées\n- Le code est automatiquement mis en majuscules\n- Limite de débit : 5 req/min sur `/promo-codes/validate` (rate limiter)\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `admin_token`, `client_token`, `driver_token`\n- `promo_id_percent` (code % créé)\n- `promo_id_fixed` (code fixe créé)\n- `client_user_id` (pour les tests de contrôle d'accès)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",        "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",     "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "promo_id_percent","value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "promo_id_fixed",  "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_user_id",  "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Setup — Tokens",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', data.access_token);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Client",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"client@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Client1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('client_token', data.access_token);",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('client_user_id', data.user?.id ?? '');"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Driver1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', data.access_token);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "⚙️ Admin — CRUD Codes Promo",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "① GET /admin/promo-codes — liste initiale",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/promo-codes?page=1&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","promo-codes"],
              "query": [{ "key": "page", "value": "1" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "20" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Structure paginée', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data.promo_codes).to.be.an('array');",
            "  pm.expect(data.total).to.be.a('number');",
            "  pm.expect(data.page).to.equal(1);",
            "  console.log('Codes existants:', data.total);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "① GET /admin/promo-codes?is_active=true — filtrer actifs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/promo-codes?is_active=true&page=1&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin","promo-codes"],
              "query": [{ "key": "is_active", "value": "true" }, { "key": "page", "value": "1" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "20" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Tous les codes retournés sont actifs', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  data.promo_codes.forEach(c => pm.expect(c.is_active).to.be.true);",
            "  console.log('Codes actifs:', data.total);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
